    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p>\n<p>Boil a full kettle</p>\n<p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>roughly</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-bangin-chilli-and-garlic-tenderstem-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-bangin-chilli-and-garlic-tenderstem-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the courgette softens, add the <strong>quick cook spaghetti </strong>and<strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">T</span>enderstem broccoli </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite, then drain</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-bangin-chilli-and-garlic-tenderstem-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the spaghetti and broccoli are cooking, dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Add the<strong> roasted garlic paste</strong> – this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-bangin-chilli-and-garlic-tenderstem-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half</p>\n<p>Cut <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-bangin-chilli-and-garlic-tenderstem-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> and <strong>Tenderstem</strong> to the <span class=\"text-highlight\">courgette</span> pan with the <strong>chilli flakes</strong>,<strong> baby spinach</strong> and <strong>stock </strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly and the spinach has wilted</p>\n<p>Squeeze in the <strong>juice</strong> from the <strong>lemon half<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">– this is your</span> <strong>chilli &amp; garlic Tenderstem spaghetti</strong></p>",
